Subject: Re: [T2] lifter question

Matty Kirk sends:

> on a 76 2.0 FI Type IV engine, can you change the
> lifters (ie. remove old, and replace with new) without
> cracking the case?

You can do it on any Type 4--pull the pushrods and pushrod tubes, use a
mechanic's magnet to pull the old lifters out and stick the new ones in.
Reassemble and drive.
